Ezemvelo KZN Wildlife has caught more crocodiles than those that had escaped from the Crocodile Creek Farm in Tongaat, north of Durban. Ezemvelo said they were informed that about 12 crocodiles were washed away during the KZN floods last week. ALSO READ |Â Crocodiles on the loose in Tongaat However, on their Facebook page, Ezemvelo reported that 14 crocodiles were caught which is two more than the initial estimated 12 that were reported to have gone missing. Ezemvelo spokesperson Musa Mntambo told The Witness last week that of the 12 crocodiles that were washed away, they had initially managed to recapture seven crocodiles. A further seven crocodiles were recaptured over the weekend. A number of videos have been circulating on social media showing a crocodile next to the Tongaat River on the M4. Mntambo urged residents to contact the Ezemvelo Wildlife should they come in contact or spot a crocodile on the loose. Efforts to get hold of Mtambo and Crocodile Creek Farm owner Peter Watson were unsuccessful.